Blocks.childText: 70 HAIL, BRIGHTEST MORNING! Words from 'The Little Sower." J. M. KIEFFER. 1. Hail, brightest morning ! hail, blessed day ! From earthly cares let us now turn away Prompt in our plac - es, 2. Sing, little children ! come, raise your voice; Jesus has bless'd you, now you may rejoice; Sing, youths and maidens, CHORUS. raise every voice, Sweetly we sing and re-joice. Come let us join the soul-inspiring song, Wake sweetest strains with join in the lay, This is the Lord's Holy Day Come let us join, etc. hearts and voices strong Sing to the Sav - ior whom we a-dore, Hon - or and praise, ev - er - more. 3 Sing, loving parents, join with us too, 4 Now, with devotion, pure and sincere, In our devotions we can not spare you; Up to the Savior our spirits draw near ; Teach us the Way, the Truth, and the Life; Thank him for mercies, graciously given, Banish all envy and strife. Pardon us, Father in heaven. Come let us join, etc. Come let us join, etc. From "The Welcome."
